class Solution {
    public int hardestWorker(int n, int[][] logs) {
        int maxTime = 0;
        int minId = n;
        int prevTime = 0;
        for (int[] log : logs) {
            int id = log[0];
            int time = log[1];
            int duration = time - prevTime;
            if (duration > maxTime || (duration == maxTime && id < minId)) {
                maxTime = duration;
                minId = id;
            }
            prevTime = time;
        }
        return minId;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(m)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the logs array once, keeping track of the maximum task duration and the corresponding employee id. It updates these values whenever it encounters a task with a longer duration or the same duration but a smaller employee id.
